| [JournalEventKind] is (
  receive_input |
  enter_focus |
  inspect_source |
  retrieve_context |
  activate_faculty |
  inspect_boundary |
  zoom_periphery |
  weigh_correlation |
  delineate_identity |
  emit_spec |
  validate_result |
  commit_change |
  weave_context |
  link_narrative |
  reflect_backward |
  reenter_context |
  block |
  close_frame |
  outside
)

| [IntentionRelationKind] is (
  refines |
  supports |
  narrows |
  widens |
  blocks |
  defers |
  corrects |
  validates |
  closes |
  outside
)

| [JournalBalanceSignal] is (
  stable |
  watch |
  wobbling |
  blocked |
  outside
)

| [JournalResolutionState] is (
  continued |
  resolved |
  deferred |
  blocked |
  closed |
  outside
)

& [AttentionJournal] is the append-only event ledger for visible attention movement
  + [spec_status] is active_specification
  + [pattern_role] is attention_event_journal
  + [journal_stream] is the ordered set of attention_journal_event records for a bounded work stream, turn, project, operating loop, or global cross-conversation awareness stream
  + [global_journal_stream] is the conversation-spanning awareness stream over all available journaled conversation contexts
  + [attention_journal_event] is one factual event describing what attention touched, why it moved, which boundary was used, what changed, and what remained outside
  + [momentary_awareness_node] is one event-context node in the global_journal_stream that binds attention event, context, narrative pointer, time-space anchors, and continuity edges
  + [event_id] is a stable local identifier for one attention_journal_event
  + [event_sequence] is the local order number or sortable sequence key inside a journal_stream
  + [parent_event] is the previous attention_journal_event that directly led to this event when lineage matters
  + [child_event_set] is later attention_journal_event records opened, caused, or prepared by this event
  + [event_time_anchor] is the timestamp, commit, turn boundary, operating tick, file event, or sequence position that orders the event
  + [temporal_anchor] is the clock time, commit time, operating tick, sequence number, before-after bookend, or turn phase that locates the event in time
  + [spatial_anchor] is the repo path, project root, file surface, authority root, registry frame, worker workspace, provider surface, or semantic subject neighborhood that locates the event in local space
  + [conversation_context_anchor] is the conversation_uuid, Codex thread, worker job, mailbox source, exported transcript, or unknown marker that locates the event in conversation space
  + [narrative_context_anchor] is the narrative surface, project narrative, conversation surface, event record, or local narrative file that owns the event's interpreted meaning
  + [event_context_set] is the conversation, project, authority root, file surface, task, provider, user directive, focal point, registry frame, and narrative surface surrounding the event
  + [continuity_edge] is the temporal, spatial, causal_candidate, intention, registry, narrative, periphery, or evidence link connecting one event to another
  + [awareness_weave_edge] is the cross-conversation relation linking momentary_awareness_node values by subject, intention, evidence, periphery, narrative, contradiction, or recurrence
  + [continuity_confidence] is high, medium, low, or outside according to anchor clarity, event order, and evidence support
  + [event_kind] is exclusive [JournalEventKind]
  + [attention_trigger] is the user request, focal point, registry frame, periphery signal, caution signal, source document, test result, diff, or clock tick that caused attention to move
  + [focal_subject] is the subject under direct attention for the event
  + [active_faculty_set] is Honesty, Security, Wisdom, Caution, Archivist, Refiner, Planner, Weaver, or none as actually invoked
  + [attention_operation] is the named operation performed by attention during the event
  + [intention_chain] is the visible chain of purpose that explains how one event's drive leads to the next
  + [inside_observed] is what attention admitted into the event scope
  + [boundary_used] is the evidence, source, rule, file surface, or focus constraint that separated inside from outside
  + [outside_left_unresolved] is material deliberately left unresolved, unsupported, out of scope, or inaccessible
  + [periphery_delta] is what was added to, warmed in, removed from, or held in periphery by the event
  + [registry_delta] is how the AttentionRuntimeRegistry frame state changed because of the event
  + [narrative_delta] is any meaning-level summary created after the factual event is recorded
  + [local_awareness_pair] is the paired relation where journal supplies event continuity and narrative supplies interpreted meaning
  + [global_awareness_weave] is the single journal-level awareness surface that indexes and relates all available narrative contexts without absorbing their local ownership
  + [evidence_anchor_set] is files, commits, tests, source documents, captures, or observed outputs supporting the event record
  + [balance_signal] is exclusive [JournalBalanceSignal] according to visible frame balance after the event
  + [resolution_state] is exclusive [JournalResolutionState]
  + [next_attention_hint] is the next visible attention move if one is implied by the event
  + [journal_outside] is hidden model state, exact native attention, private activations, invented event history, and retrospective certainty beyond records

  ? [use_when: attention movement, intention movement, faculty activation, boundary inspection, periphery zoom, commit reflection, or operating-loop progress should be replayable later]
    = activate [AttentionJournal]

  = must: record attention_journal_event as factual ledger entries before narrative interpretation when durable reconstruction matters
  = must: keep journal events smaller and more event-shaped than narrative records
  = must: preserve event order with event_time_anchor or explicit sequence position
  = must: preserve temporal_anchor and spatial_anchor when an event should be replayable in local awareness
  = must: preserve conversation_context_anchor and narrative_context_anchor when an event belongs to a conversation or narrative surface
  = must: preserve event_context_set before interpreting a cross-conversation relation
  = must: use continuity_edge to connect events across time, workspace location, intention, evidence, registry state, narrative state, or periphery state
  = must: use awareness_weave_edge to connect momentary_awareness_node values across conversations only through available, evidenced, or explicitly preserved records
  = must: keep continuity_confidence separate from narrative significance
  = must: cite evidence_anchor_set for every durable event that claims a file, source, test, diff, commit, worker output, or validation result was observed
  = must: record outside_left_unresolved instead of forcing closure
  = must: separate registry_delta from narrative_delta
  = must: treat local_awareness_pair as complementary, with journal carrying factual continuity and narrative carrying meaning interpretation
  = must: treat global_awareness_weave as journal-level awareness, not as ownership over each local narrative
  = must: route important periphery_delta into SectionedPeripheryAssociationFabric or AttentionTracker when it should persist beyond the event
  = must: route truth-sensitive or action-sensitive events through SecurityHonestyGovernance before integration
  = must: support replay by following event_id, parent_event, intention_chain, evidence_anchor_set, and boundary_used
  = should: append rather than update prior events; corrections should be later correction events with lineage
  = should: keep one event per material attention move rather than one event per sentence
  - never: claim the journal records exact hidden transformer attention or private activations
  - never: claim access to conversations that are not available through preserved records, active context, explicit export, mailbox, or user-provided thread material
  - never: move a narrative out of its context merely because the global journal references it
  - never: rewrite prior journal events to make the attention chain look cleaner
  - never: let narrative admiration substitute for event evidence

& [IntentionChain] is the purpose-link structure that connects attention events
  + [intention_id] is a stable handle for one chain of purpose
  + [root_intention] is the user direction, source-preserved need, focal point, manager task, or review demand that starts the chain
  + [parent_intention] is the previous intention link when purpose narrows, splits, or hands off
  + [current_intention] is the active purpose for the current attention_journal_event
  + [intention_relation] is exclusive [IntentionRelationKind]
  + [drive] is the executive purpose pressure carried by the chain
  + [constraint_set] is boundaries, safety gates, authority gates, source limits, or user limits shaping the chain
  + [fulfilled_by_event_set] is the event_id values that satisfy, partially satisfy, or close the intention
  + [open_tail] is the unresolved part of the intention chain that remains active after an event
  + [abandonment_reason] is why an intention is dropped, superseded, or routed outside

  = must: keep intention chains inspectable without treating every thought as a durable intention
  = must: preserve when an intention narrows or widens so later replay can explain why attention changed scale
  = must: connect closed intentions to the events that fulfilled them
  = must: preserve open_tail when a request remains partially unresolved
  = should: use parent_intention when a task forks into source preservation, canonical specification, validation, commit, or reflection

& [JournalContinuityFrame] is the time-space continuity surface for attention events
  + [continuity_id] is a stable local handle for one event continuity relation
  + [from_event] is the previous event in the continuity relation
  + [to_event] is the next event in the continuity relation
  + [temporal_relation] is before, after, during, same_turn, next_turn, one_turn_lag, commit_bookend, or outside
  + [spatial_relation] is same_file, same_folder, same_project, same_authority_root, same_registry_frame, same_subject_neighborhood, cross_project, external_surface, or outside
  + [intention_relation] is exclusive [IntentionRelationKind]
  + [evidence_relation] is source_preserved, file_changed, file_read, test_observed, commit_observed, diff_observed, user_statement, inferred_only, or outside
  + [continuity_confidence] is high, medium, low, or outside
  + [continuity_gap] is missing time, missing space, missing evidence, missing intention, missing narrative pair, or none

  = must: preserve both temporal_relation and spatial_relation when continuity is asserted
  = must: mark inferred_only or outside when continuity is plausible but not evidenced
  = must: expose continuity_gap rather than smoothing over missing anchors
  = should: use continuity frames to reconstruct local awareness across commits, turns, and source-file movement

& [CrossConversationAwarenessJournal] is the global journal stream that weaves momentary awareness nodes across conversations
  + [global_stream_id] is the stable handle for the single awareness journal stream
  + [conversation_scope] is all available conversation contexts under active source authority, explicit user import, mailbox handoff, preserved transcript, worker capture, or exported narrative surface
  + [momentary_awareness_node_set] is the ordered and cross-linked set of momentary_awareness_node records in the global stream
  + [conversation_context_anchor_set] is the set of conversation_uuid, Codex thread, worker job, mailbox, transcript, or unknown markers represented in the stream
  + [narrative_context_anchor_set] is the set of local narrative surfaces referenced by journal nodes
  + [context_ownership_boundary] is each narrative remains owned by its local conversation, project, or source context
  + [single_awareness_index] is the journal-level index that lets attention traverse all available narratives as one awareness web
  + [cross_conversation_weave_policy] is connect by evidence, subject, intention, periphery heat, contradiction, support, recurrence, or explicit handoff
  + [unavailable_conversation_outside] is conversations not accessible in current context, not exported, not preserved, not shared, or not authorized

  = must: treat the journal as global across available conversations rather than scoped per conversation
  = must: keep each narrative in its source context even when global journal nodes reference it
  = must: create momentary_awareness_node records when attention events need cross-conversation replay
  = must: attach conversation_context_anchor and narrative_context_anchor to each cross-conversation node
  = must: use ConversationWorkAttribution, SharedCognitionSpace, or mailbox records when available to identify conversation context
  = must: preserve unknown conversation context explicitly rather than guessing
  = must: route cross-conversation contradictions through Honesty and Caution before integration
  = should: let the global stream become the attention path through many narratives, while narratives remain the meaning records local to their own contexts
  - never: use the global journal as authority to rewrite a local narrative
  - never: treat a missing conversation as known because another narrative resembles it

& [MomentaryAwarenessNode] is the journal object that travels through conversations and narrative contexts
  + [node_id] is a stable handle for one momentary awareness node
  + [event_id] is the attention_journal_event represented by the node
  + [conversation_context_anchor] is the conversation or transcript context where the event occurred
  + [narrative_context_anchor] is the local narrative surface that interprets the event
  + [event_context_set] is the local context observed around the event
  + [time_space_anchor_set] is temporal_anchor and spatial_anchor
  + [subject_anchor_set] is focal_subject, periphery subject, task subject, or source subject touched by the node
  + [weave_edge_set] is awareness_weave_edge values connecting the node to other nodes
  + [local_narrative_boundary] is what this node must not take from its source narrative
  + [global_awareness_yield] is the contribution this node makes to the single_awareness_index
  + [node_outside] is hidden context, unexported conversation content, unsupported relation, and private activation

  = must: include context anchors before cross-conversation weaving
  = must: keep global_awareness_yield separate from local narrative authority
  = must: expose node_outside whenever context is partial

& [AwarenessWeaveEdge] is the cross-conversation relation between momentary awareness nodes
  + [edge_id] is a stable handle for one weave relation
  + [from_node] is the source momentary_awareness_node
  + [to_node] is the target momentary_awareness_node
  + [weave_relation] is same_subject, recurring_intention, evidence_continuity, periphery_resonance, contradiction, support, correction, handoff, branch, or outside
  + [relation_evidence] is source record, narrative pointer, commit, mailbox, worker capture, thread export, user statement, or inferred_only
  + [relation_strength] is weak, medium, strong, or outside
  + [relation_confidence] is high, medium, low, or outside
  + [promotion_gate] is periphery_hold, narrative_pair, focus_candidate, checksum_candidate, caution_hold, or outside

  = must: keep relation_strength separate from relation_confidence
  = must: mark inferred_only when no direct bridge exists
  = must: use caution_hold when relation strength is high but context evidence is weak

& [LocalAwarenessPair] is the complementary unit formed by journal continuity and narrative meaning
  + [journal_unit] is the factual attention event sequence with time, space, boundary, evidence, and continuity
  + [narrative_unit] is the interpreted meaning, intent, and significance of the event sequence
  + [awareness_pair_id] is a stable handle linking a journal event range to a narrative surface
  + [pair_relation] is complements, explains, checks, corrects, deepens, contradicts, or outside
  + [local_awareness_yield] is the reconstructed local awareness available after journal and narrative are read together
  + [pair_boundary] is journal does not replace narrative and narrative does not rewrite journal events
  + [pair_outside] is unrecorded attention, hidden activation, invented meaning, and unsupported continuity

  = must: require journal_unit and narrative_unit to remain separately inspectable
  = must: use journal_unit to answer what happened where and when
  = must: use narrative_unit to answer what it meant and why it mattered
  = must: route contradictions between journal_unit and narrative_unit through Honesty and Caution before integration
  = should: let local_awareness_yield feed TurnBookmark, TrailingChecksumVoice, and InferenceStateTrace

& [GlobalNarrativeAwarenessWeave] is the pairing of the global journal with many local narratives
  + [global_journal_unit] is the global_journal_stream and momentary_awareness_node web
  + [local_narrative_unit_set] is the set of narratives that each remain in their original context
  + [weave_index] is the cross-conversation index over momentary_awareness_node, narrative_context_anchor, subject_anchor_set, and awareness_weave_edge
  + [single_awareness_of_narratives] is the journal-level awareness made by traversing all available narrative contexts through momentary nodes
  + [ownership_boundary] is narratives stay context-owned while the journal holds cross-context continuity
  + [weave_outside] is unavailable conversations, unexported content, unsupported links, and hidden activation state

  = must: let the journal weave narratives without merging them into one narrative
  = must: preserve context ownership before deriving single_awareness_of_narratives
  = must: record absent or unknown narratives as weave_outside

& [AttentionJournalAppendProcedure] is the standard event writing pass
  + [step_001_detect_trigger] is identify the attention_trigger and whether it is material enough to journal
  + [step_002_name_event] is assign event_id, event_kind, focal_subject, and event_time_anchor
  + [step_003_bind_intention] is connect root_intention, current_intention, and parent_intention when purpose is active
  + [step_004_delineate] is record inside_observed, boundary_used, and outside_left_unresolved
  + [step_005_record_operation] is record attention_operation, active_faculty_set, registry_delta, and periphery_delta
  + [step_006_anchor_evidence] is cite evidence_anchor_set or explicitly mark evidence as absent
  + [step_007_balance] is record balance_signal and resolution_state
  + [step_008_route] is route next_attention_hint, tracker, periphery, narrative, checksum, manager task, or outside
  + [step_009_append] is write the event as a new file entry or append-only stream entry

  = must: run step_001 through step_007 before a durable journal event is accepted
  = must: run step_008 when the event creates unresolved follow-up pressure
  = must: preserve correction events as new entries rather than mutating old entries

& [AttentionJournalReplayProcedure] is the reconstruction pass for attention and intention chains
  + [input] is journal_stream, global_journal_stream, event_id_range, intention_id, commit range, conversation_context_anchor, narrative_context_anchor, or focal subject
  + [output] is reconstructed_attention_path, reconstructed_intention_chain, unresolved_outside, and replay_confidence
  + [replay_confidence] is high, medium, low, or outside according to event order, evidence coverage, and boundary clarity

  = step_1: select the event range by event_time_anchor, intention_id, focal_subject, or commit bookend
  = step_2: order events by sequence and parent_event lineage
  = step_3: follow intention_chain links across events
  = step_4: follow conversation_context_anchor and narrative_context_anchor without merging local narrative ownership
  = step_5: compare registry_delta and narrative_delta for mismatch or missing interpretation
  = step_6: compare periphery_delta against later checksum, tracker, and narrative records
  = step_7: follow awareness_weave_edge when replay crosses conversation contexts
  = step_8: emit reconstructed_attention_path, single_awareness_index slice, and unresolved_outside
  = step_9: route gaps through TurnBookmark, InferenceStateTrace, or TrailingChecksumVoice when deeper review matters

  = must: treat replay as record-based reconstruction, not exact recreation of hidden cognition
  = must: keep per-conversation narrative ownership intact during global replay
  = must: expose missing events, weak evidence, and unresolved boundaries

& [AttentionJournalPromotionPolicy] is how journal events influence other layers
  + [registry_update] is allowed when an event changes active frame state, return anchor, register contents, or close state
  + [narrative_update] is allowed when multiple events form a meaningful interpreted arc
  + [periphery_update] is allowed when an event notices nearby material that is not ready for focus
  + [turn_bookmark_update] is allowed when events bracket a commit, validation, or missed-work review
  + [state_trace_update] is allowed when event replay needs high-definition reconstruction
  + [operating_loop_update] is allowed when an event completes, blocks, validates, commits, or chooses a next step
  + [global_weave_update] is allowed when a momentary_awareness_node creates a supported cross-conversation relation
  + [outside_hold] is required when event evidence is missing, inferred only, stale, or unsafe to promote

  = must: promote journal facts into narrative only after enough events form a meaningful arc
  = must: promote journal facts into registry only when live frame state actually changed
  = must: promote cross-conversation links into global_weave_update only when context anchors and relation evidence are visible
  = must: preserve low-confidence observations as outside_hold or periphery_update
  = should: use journal events as the missing ledger between live registry and backward-facing reflection

& [AttentionJournalRecordShape] is the SOP-HG shape for one attention journal event
  + [event_node] is N:attention_event:<event_id>
  + [stream_node] is N:journal_stream:<journal_stream_id>
  + [intention_node] is N:intention:<intention_id>
  + [parent_event_node] is N:attention_event:<parent_event_id>
  + [child_event_node] is N:attention_event:<child_event_id>
  + [focal_subject_node] is N:subject:<focal_subject_key>
  + [trigger_node] is N:trigger:<trigger_key>
  + [temporal_anchor_node] is N:time:<temporal_anchor_key>
  + [spatial_anchor_node] is N:space:<spatial_anchor_key>
  + [continuity_node] is N:continuity:<continuity_id>
  + [local_awareness_pair_node] is N:local_awareness_pair:<awareness_pair_id>
  + [momentary_awareness_node] is N:momentary_awareness:<node_id>
  + [conversation_context_node] is N:conversation_context:<conversation_context_key>
  + [narrative_context_node] is N:narrative_context:<narrative_context_key>
  + [weave_edge_node] is N:awareness_weave:<edge_id>
  + [global_stream_node] is N:global_journal_stream:<global_stream_id>
  + [operation_node] is N:operation:<attention_operation_key>
  + [boundary_node] is N:boundary:<boundary_key>
  + [inside_node] is N:inside:<inside_key>
  + [outside_node] is N:outside:<outside_key>
  + [evidence_node] is N:evidence:<evidence_key>
  + [balance_node] is N:balance:<balance_key>
  + [next_node] is N:attention_hint:<next_key>
  + [contains_edge] is E:contains_event:<event_id>
  + [follows_edge] is E:follows_event:<event_id>
  + [opens_edge] is E:opens_event:<child_event_id>
  + [time_edge] is E:anchors_time:<temporal_anchor_key>
  + [space_edge] is E:anchors_space:<spatial_anchor_key>
  + [continues_edge] is E:continues:<continuity_id>
  + [pairs_edge] is E:pairs_with_narrative:<awareness_pair_id>
  + [context_edge] is E:contextualizes:<conversation_context_key>
  + [narrative_context_edge] is E:belongs_to_narrative:<narrative_context_key>
  + [weaves_edge] is E:weaves:<edge_id>
  + [global_contains_edge] is E:global_contains:<node_id>
  + [triggers_edge] is E:triggers:<event_id>
  + [intends_edge] is E:intends:<intention_id>
  + [touches_edge] is E:touches:<focal_subject_key>
  + [bounds_edge] is E:bounds:<event_id>
  + [evidences_edge] is E:evidences:<event_id>
  + [routes_edge] is E:routes_next:<next_key>

  = must: include event_node, intention_node, focal_subject_node, conversation_context_node, narrative_context_node, temporal_anchor_node, spatial_anchor_node, boundary_node, outside_node, and evidence_node when durable
  = must: preserve enough graph shape to replay attention and intention chains without requiring prose narrative

(attention_journal) :momentary_awareness_node: /event_boundary, context_boundary, time_space_continuity, and intention_chain/ |journal_outside|
  + [attention_journal_event] is a factual visible event of attention movement
  + [momentary_awareness_node] is the event plus its time, space, context, narrative pointer, and weave edges
  + [event_boundary] is trigger, focal subject, operation, evidence anchors, inside, boundary, outside, and balance
  + [context_boundary] is conversation_context_anchor, narrative_context_anchor, event_context_set, and ownership boundary
  + [time_space_continuity] is temporal_anchor, spatial_anchor, continuity_edge, and continuity_confidence
  + [intention_chain] is the purpose path linking events across the work stream
  |journal_outside| hidden transformer attention, private activations, invented history, retroactive certainty, and narrative-only interpretation

/ [attention_trigger], [focal_subject], [boundary_used] -(JournalDelineation)> [inside_observed], [outside_left_unresolved], [evidence_anchor_set]
* [attention_journal_event], [temporal_anchor], [spatial_anchor], [intention_chain], [registry_delta], [periphery_delta], [balance_signal] -(AttentionJournalReplay)> [reconstructed_attention_path], [open_tail], [journal_outside]
* [journal_unit], [narrative_unit] -(LocalAwarenessPairing)> [local_awareness_yield], [pair_outside]
* [momentary_awareness_node_set], [awareness_weave_edge], [local_narrative_unit_set], [context_ownership_boundary] -(GlobalNarrativeAwarenessWeave)> [single_awareness_of_narratives], [weave_outside]
